# .shopifyignore — files Shopify CLI must not push or pull.
# Syntax: bare paths (templates/*.bak), * wildcards (*.jpg, config/*_secret.json),
# or /regex/ (/\.(zip|tar)$/).
#
# NOTE: .shopifyignore is bidirectional — it blocks both push AND pull. Don't
# list config/settings_data.json here: it would also block pulling the live
# store's customizer settings (e.g. the shopify-theme-pull workflow). To keep a
# push from clobbering merchant settings, pass `--ignore config/settings_data.json`
# on the push command instead.

# Repo tooling and source that aren't theme files — keep the CLI from pushing
# them to the live theme (or touching them on pull). Reconcile to your repo's
# actual layout.
node_modules/**
src/**
scripts/**
tests/**
test-results/**
.github/**
.git/**
package.json
package-lock.json
pnpm-lock.yaml
yarn.lock
bun.lockb
tsconfig.json
biome.json
vite.config.*
.env*
README*

# Build leftovers that shouldn't ship to the live theme.
assets/*.map

# OS cruft that can sneak into assets/.
*.DS_Store
